[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/slamo 
		"slamo
	]a
	": This run uses an older version of ScummVM, so I decided to investigate the compatibility of Myst: ME with ScummVM. Here's a timeline of events:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" The game was officially supported with 
		[a href=https://www.scummvm.org/compatibility/1.9.0/mystme/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
			""Untested"
		]a
		" compatibility at 
		[a href=https://github.com/scummvm/scummvm/blob/master/NEWS.md#190-myst-ery-ufos-release-2016-10-17 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"1.9.0's release
		]a
		" on 2016-10-17.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Version 
		[a href=https://github.com/scummvm/scummvm/blob/master/NEWS.md#200-2017-12-17 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"2.0.0
		]a
		", the version used in this run, was released on 2017-12-17. Myst: ME has gained 
		[a href=https://www.scummvm.org/compatibility/2.0.0/mystme/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
			""Good"
		]a
		" compatibility at this point (which it still has at the time of writing this).
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" The official releases of Myst: ME started using ScummVM, 
		[a href=https://support.gog.com/hc/en-us/articles/360002696774-Myst-Masterpiece-Edition-Update-to-ScummVM-and-change-in-save-files?product=gog rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"GoG on 2018-04-04
		]a
		" and 
		[a href=https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/63660?emclan=103582791433475906&emgid=2883948831518841809 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"Steam
		]a
		" later that year.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" The next official version of ScummVM, 
		[a href=https://github.com/scummvm/scummvm/blob/master/NEWS.md#210-electric-sheep-2019-10-11 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"2.1.0
		]a
		", was released on 2019-10-11, and is currently being used for the official releases. The changelog lists some bug fixes for Myst.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" There have been some changes to how ScummVM handles Myst since then, such as a feature to 
		[a href=https://github.com/scummvm/scummvm/pull/3129 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"simulate CD loading times
		]a
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Given this timeline, it's reasonable to believe that the official releases were using ScummVM 2.0.0 to run Myst when they were made available (and for at least a year after that), and if it was good enough for an official version of the game, then it's good enough for us. The platform being Windows is appropriate because this movie uses files from the Windows version and, rather unbelievably, there has never been an official Linux release (even though the Windows and Mac version use ScummVM and it could have been ported!?)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Other than all that, optimization looks good of course, and it's nice to finally have a somewhat original version of Myst on the site. Accepting.
	$LF
]div
